&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Brief Description of the Role: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is an exciting opportunity for an ambitious and talented individual, to be part of our ambition to be an outstanding organization. We are looking for a motivated individual with a passion for excellence, who can help take the Education service forward for Bradford Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will have the opportunity to develop and implement new ways of working to continually drive quality for the benefit of our trust, work closely with our neighboring trusts and help further our already great relationships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an acute Trust delivering services, teaching and research to over 500,000 people in Bradford and some specialist care to over 1 million people in the west of West Yorkshire. We have recently been inspected by the CQC and have a rating of Good, our ambition is to be outstanding. We actively collaborate with our partners in one of the largest ICS footprints in the country, and we’re working towards the greater integration of services in our local place, Bradford Districts &amp; Craven.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carly Wilson. Education Lead - Business Support and Governance, carly.wilson@bthft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer staff gymnasiums on both hospital sites, excellent pension scheme and advice on childcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 11.11.20 (This date may change dependent on the response)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
